From 582f5be9efde57ed3fa9099ca8c93a70f006c5a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 15:49:43 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Diff view: patch-direct rendering, lazy composer, gutter
 hover affordance
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three issues with the previous patch-reconstructed flow, all rooted
in the same place — we padded inter-hunk gaps with empty strings so
model lines == file lines, then leaned on `hideUnchangedRegions` to
collapse the blanks. That meant: (1) clicking the "+ N hidden lines"
expand button revealed the padding blanks; (2) clicking the gutter
to add a comment kicked off a full `renderLoaded` rebuild of every
diff editor in the stack, ~100s of ms of lag; (3) no visual cue that
the gutter was clickable at all.

- Patch-direct reconstruction (`krtPatchReconstruct.ts` v2): each
  model line corresponds to one real patch row. No padding, no
  inter-hunk gaps. Per-side `realLines: (number | undefined)[]` map
  records the file's actual line number for each model line, so the
  gutter still displays e.g. 549, 550, … even though the model is
  compact.
- `KrtMonacoDiffView`: disabled `hideUnchangedRegions`, fed the
  per-side maps into `getOriginalEditor().updateOptions({ lineNumbers
  })` and `getModifiedEditor().updateOptions(...)` so each gutter
  shows the real file number. `addLineZone` now translates real-line
  → model-line internally; review-comment threads still anchor to
  file lines as before.
- `mountComposer(side, line, dom)` / `dismountComposer()` — replace
  the renderLoaded-on-click pattern. The click handler builds the
  composer DOM and mounts it as a single view zone in place. Cancel
  dismounts the zone without re-rendering. Submit still does a full
  re-render after the network call (it has to refresh the comment
  list anyway).
- Gutter hover affordance via CSS — line-numbers turn accent-coloured
  with an accent-soft background on hover, signaling click-to-comment.

Net: clicking a line opens the composer instantly; expanding hidden
regions is moot (none exist with the new reconstruction); hover
makes the click target discoverable.
